summary:
Taylor Swift lookbook
We all know that Tay can ace any outfit anytime, but however I would still like to present you my favorite...
body:
Taylor Swift lookbook

We all know that Tay can ace any outfit anytime, but however I would still like to present you my favorite styles of hers through the years 💕 (before the reputation era)


I love Taylor’s on-stage outfits to the moon and back. Here’s one iconic outfit from 1989 tour and a few from her other performances like Victoria’s Secret fashion show. I love that combination of black and glitter on her.


These two iconic outfits are a little nod to the reputation era. I think that both outfits look kinda poisonous, snake-like and dangerous in a very stylish way. (Watch out for Taylor Swift) In addition to clothes Taylor can also rock any hairstyle, like for example this magnificent Bleach-Taylor look. #bleachella


Taylor’s street style is casual and comfortable but classy at the same time. Pictures 1 & 2 (from the left) remind me of Kate Middleton and Taylor indeed looks like royalty in them. Ponchos and two-pieces have always been a clear part of Taylor’s style and not to forget the keystone alias red lipstick.


Here’s a bunch of Taylor’s gala gowns. Both blue and red suit her well. Her two Grammy dresses (top left) are stylistically very similar to each other but still so different. My favorite out of these all is the blue one on the bottom right.


And some shorter dresses too. The blue one from 2013 BMA’s is absolutely unique and very pretty.


And finally the last one which includes my favorite two-pieces and trouser suits. Back in 2014 I still wasn’t a huge fan of Taylor’s and didn’t know that much about her even though I had been listening to her music and watching her music videos from YouTube for ages. I remember admiring her style and especially those two-piece outfits like this green one from Teen Choice Awards here. This gorgeous VMA’s 2014 blue suit is one of my favorites of all the time.


Thank you for reading! 💛

summary: Yesterday I was out to eat at an Italian restaurant with my grandma. I was in the middle of telling her how I would be seeing...
body:
Yesterday I was out to eat at an Italian restaurant with my grandma. I was in the middle of telling her how I would be seeing @taylorswift soon, as I hear over the speakers a Jazzy version of Blank Space. This isn’t the only time weird things like this happen to me with you, Taylor. I was in CVS picking up my prescriptions on Saturday, and faintly I hear playing throughout the store the “ah ah ah ah ahhh” from the beginning of New Romantics. Also, not the first time something like that has happened to me in a store, happens all the damn time. For years now. I could be listening to you on Spotify, unplug it from my phone and then would ya look at that right on the radio when I unplug.


I think the universe is telling us that we have to meet. It’s literally causing a rift in the universal code, that now I can’t go anywhere without you following me. I try not to talk about it, but it’s true. @taylornation I believe you’re the people that also need to do something about this. Hook this situation up.
